<statement>
<p>Which of the following is largest amount (rather than largest percent)? </p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>32<percent/> of 132</li> 
<li>94<percent/> of 64</li> 
<li>4<percent/> of 2445</li> 
</ol></p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>C: 4<percent/> of 2445</li></ul></p><p>We must first calculate (or at least approximate) each value.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{94}\%\cdot{64}={60.16}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{32}\%\cdot{132}={42.24}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{4}\%\cdot{2445}={97.8}</m></p>
<p>From these calculations we see that 4<percent/> of 2445 is the largest.</p>

</solution>
